title: Sampler
medium:
Medium: linen and silk
Technique: embroidery (for pattern only)
description:
Geometric stepped fret in each corner with floral vines.  Top has sun with flowers on each side.  

Sampler reads: "Since all the downward tracts of time/ Gods watchfull eye surveys/ Or who so wise to chuse our lot/ And regulate our ways/ Since none can doubt his equal love/ Unmeasurably kind/To his unerring gracious will/Be every wish resigned."

Signed: "Maria Handsley (?) 1810."
name: Sampler
